CIC/References/ContentTemplates/Text.htm.body:
Text template
Displays text on a screen. It is used to display text with highlights, paragraph text or table text.

Note!
See Screen UI example for available display formats of the Text template.


Template field



Field name
Type
Field description
Required




bgUrl
URLObject
An object containing the URL of the image to display in background
No


highlightText
StringObject or NumberObject
An object containing text or number to highlight. You can add a digit grouping symbol to numbers.
No


imageUrl
URLObject
An object containing the URL of the image
No


linkUrl
URLObject
An object containing a URL which directs users to a web map when a map image is included
No


mainText
StringObject
An object containing main text
No


paragraphText
StringObject
An object containing paragraph text
No


referenceText
StringObject
An object containing text data of the source
No


referenceURL
URLObject
An object containing the URL of the source
No


sentenceText
StringObject
An object containing sentence text
No


subText
StringObject
An object containing sub text
No


tableList[]
object array
An object array containing table text. The table consists of two columns.
No


tableList[].item1
StringObject
An object containing text to display in the first column
No


tableList[].item2
StringObject
An object containing text to display in the second column
No


tableList[].item2Link
URLObject or PhoneNumberObject
An object containing link URL or phone number for the text in the second column
No


type
string
A content template delimiter. The value is always "ImageText".
Yes



Template Example
// Example 1.
// User request: 1달러 지금 얼마야? (User asks how much 1 dollar is worth now. Text with highlights is displayed)
{
  "actionList": [
    {
      "type": "action",
      "value": ""
    }
  ],
  "bgUrl": {
    "type": "url",
    "value": ""
  },
  "highlightText": {
    "type": "number",
    "value": "1,119"
  },
  "mainText": {
    "type": "string",
